snippet.textDisplay:
Dhondoo chahe jitna bi apne jahan mein
milon gi kahan mein to hun asaman mein

I felt this song is speaking from the perspective of nature and life communicating its feelings with us.
This song tells us what life is, the old temple overtaken by nature, and the eternal message of the universe about our identity.
When the first singer sang love, the resonance caused the nature around him to grow so quickly in case you noticed.
The reality is we are nature, a part of nature, when one part of nature gets damaged we all bear the pain, we are not isolated or separate, we are all one, connected, and grown by love and care.

Thank You Coke Studio for such a rich and wonderful message.
